false incident_record_producer /sc_cat_item_producer_list.do?sysparm_query=name%3DCreate%20Incident 3 1 1c4d6d1025913200964f48ca4b89e82b false true The Self-Service Portal empowers users to submit requests, find information, log, and manage their own incidents. An effective implementation of the Service Portal can help reduce the number of calls and emails to Service Desk.

The following screenshot displays the record producer Create Incident:

Figure 1. Create Incident record producer

Update the record producer Create Incident by adding the following variables:

 Field Description Comments
 Requester Person requesting assistance with an issue. Populated with information from the logged in user.
 Affected  User Person affected by the incident. Default value is the same as Requester, but can be updated.


All fields on the self-service form are required to create an incident.

Update the record producer Create Incident, which is available in the category Can we help you? based on proven process recommendations. 

  1. To configure the record producer, navigate to Service Catalog > Record Producers > Create Incident
  2. Add the following new variables and set all variables to mandatory:
     Field  Description
     Requester Populate with logged in user.
     Affected user Populate with logged in user.
  3. Map the record producer variables to the following incident fields:
     Variable Field
     Affected user Affected user
     Comments Short description: limit of 160 characters.
     Comments Description: no limit of characters.
